---

What is this:
Animator is ment to create smother animations when possible. It uses
requestAnimationFrame as callback routine.

See:
http://webstuff.nfshost.com/anim-timing/Overview.html
https://developer.mozilla.org/en/DOM/window.requestAnimationFrame
http://dev.chromium.org/developers/design-documents/requestanimationframe-implementation

---

The interface:

Starts the animation loop, if not already running
void:start

Stops/Pauses the animation loop, if running...
void:stop

Adds one ore many functions to the queue
Throws 'Only functions are allowed in the queue'
param:array|function
void:addToQueue

Removes a function from the queue
param:function
void:removeFromQueue

Removes an item from the queue depending on specified index
param:function
void:removeIndexFromQueue

Returns the current queue
array:getQueue

Clears the old queue and sets a new one
Throws 'Only functions are allowed in the queue'
param:array
void:setQueue 

Unsets the queue
void:clearQueue